{
  "texts": [
    "Synthetic identities have also been weaponized in the political context of elections and referendums.",
    "A retrospective look at the 2016 Brexit campaign indicated the presence of suspicious accounts later suspected to be fictitious.",
    "But in more recent electoral events, concrete evidence has emerged.",
    "In the lead-up to various elections, including the 2020 U.S. elections and others, researchers documented fake persona accounts used to deliver tailored political messages.",
    "These messages exploited voters' fears and preferences to influence their decisions."
  ]
}